healing” of migrants’ psychological pain. Richlin offers insights into the affective dimensions of migration, the strategies pursued by evangelical churches to attract migrants, and the ways in which evangelical belonging enables migrants to feel better, emboldening them to improve their lives.Looking at the ways evangelical churches help migrants navigate negative emotions, In the Hands of God sheds light on the versatility and durability of evangelical Christianity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChurch work with immigrantszUnited States. 0aEvangelicalismzUnited States. 7aRELIGION / Christian Ministry / Evangelism.2bisacsh  aEvangelical Christianity American Christianity Pentecostalism Charismatic Christianity U.S. Migration Migration Studies Brazil Brazilian migration and diaspora Brazilian religions Brazilian Pentecostalism Brazilian Christianity Affect Emotion Affect Theory Undocumented migration Latin American migration Anthropology of Religion Anthropology of Christianity Psychological Anthropology Anthropology of the U.S.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022 Englishz978311099454408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022z9783110994537oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074973140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978069123075740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691230757423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691230757/original  a978-3-11-074973-1  Princeton University Pre